## Plan de PRs atómicos (secuenciado por sprint)

1) feat(auth): add roles enums and strict types
2) feat(auth): add autoFilterByDador and authorizeTransportista
3) feat(auth): introduce PermissionsService and enforce ownership checks
4) test(auth): add RBAC and ownership contract tests
5) feat(doc): add document versioning and reject reasons
6) feat(doc): renew and history endpoints; extend approval reject
7) feat(media): add thumbnails and secure preview
8) feat(semaforo): add equipo estado service and endpoints
9) feat(client): bulk search and structured zip jobs
10) feat(zip): job orchestration and progress feedback
11) feat(ui-*): client/dador/transport/guards and flows (3–4 PRs pequeños)
12) feat(notify): email channel, templates and cron jobs
13) feat(audit): add audit log model and middleware
14) feat(obs): enrich /metrics and /health checks
15) feat(security): harden headers, cors and rate-limits
16) chore(ops): db backup/restore scripts and docs
17) docs(ops): s3 versioning and lifecycle policies

Notas:
- Mantener cada PR ≤ 400–600 LOC efectivos y con tests mínimos incluidos.
- Evitar mezclar refactors no relacionados; comentarios sólo para racionales relevantes.


